properties.areaDesc: Admiralty Inlet Area; Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca; Western Strait of Juan De Fuca
properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 11 at 2:46PM PST until January 13 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 6
inches possible.

* WHERE...Admiralty Inlet Area, including Port Townsend, Whidbey
Island, and Camano Island, Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca
lowlands, including Port Angeles, Sequim, and Blyn and Western
Strait of Juan de Fuca lowlands, including Sekiu, Clallam Bay,
and Joyce.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through late Sunday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Storm Watch means there is a potential for significant
snow, sleet, or ice accumulations that may impact travel. Continue
to monitor the latest forecasts.

Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE SUNDAY NIGHT
